  "title": "Planning Engineer",
  "description": "<p><br /><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><p>Manage, monitor, and control the overall construction schedule, including preparation and regular updates of the Master Programme.</p></li><li><p>Update planning and control documents to reflect planned works, actual progress, revised sequences, additional works, and time impacts.</p></li><li><p>Monitor site progress and resource deployment, and prepare daily, weekly, and monthly manpower and equipment reports for submission to the Client.</p></li><li><p>Issue regular progress and planning updates to Construction, Engineering, and Contract teams.</p></li><li><p>Prepare, compile, and submit Monthly Progress Reports, including maintaining site progress photographs and videos for records.</p></li><li><p>Carry out progress analysis to identify delays, assess schedule impacts, and recommend mitigation measures.</p></li><li><p>Perform delay analysis and prepare recovery programmes where required.</p></li><li><p>Prepare substantiation records and summaries for excusable delays.<br /></p><p></p></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li><p>Diploma or Degree in Civil Engineering, Construction Management, or related discipline.</p></li><li><p>Proven experience in construction planning and scheduling.</p></li><li><p>Proficient in project planning tools (e.g. Primavera P6 / MS Project).</p></li><li><p>Strong analytical, coordination, and reporting skills.</p></li></ul><p><br /></p><p>Kindly email your resume in a detailed Word format to <a href=\"mailto:faith.patman@peopleprofilers.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>faith.patman@peopleprofilers.com</strong></a></p><p>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified</p><p><strong>People Profilers Pte Ltd</strong></p><p>http://www.peopleprofilers.com<br /><br />20 Cecil Street, #08-09 PLUS Building Singapore 049705</p><p>EA License No. 02C4944</p><p>Registration No. R22107092</p>",
